-- Polysilicon Rises 3%, Most in Eight Months Last Week, BNEF Says
-- B y   M a r c   R o c a
-- 2012-01-10T09:53:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-10/polysilicon-rises-3-most-in-eight-months-last-week-bnef-says.html
The price of polysilicon, the raw
material used to make most solar panels, rose 3 percent last
week, the most in eight months, Bloomberg New Energy Finance
data shows.  The average spot price of the material increased to $27.36
per kilogram last week from $26.52, the London-based research
group said today. Prices had been falling since September, with
the only exception the second week of December. They have
skidded 61 percent in the last 12 months.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marc Roca in London at 
